== History == According to the ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'' (Chronicles of Japan), in the 5th year of [[:en:Emperor Richū|Emperor Richū]]'s reign, Kuramochi no Kimi appropriated the resources of the Kuramochibe in [[Tsukushi Province]] and seized the Kuramochibe allocated to the [[:en:Munakata Shrine|Munakata Shrine]]. As a punishment, the Kuramochibe in Tsukushi Province was confiscated.
== Provinces with Kuramochibe == Provinces where Kuramochibe were present, or are believed to have been present, include the following:<ref>Ōta Ryō, ''Seishi Kakei Jisho'' (Genealogical Dictionary of Surnames), Isobe Kōyōdō, 1920.</ref> * [[Yamato Province]] * [[Settsu Province]] (''[[Shinsen Shōjiroku]]'' records, "Kuramochi no Kimi, descendants of Toyokiiribiko no Mikoto.") * [[:en:Iga Province|Iga Province]] (associated with Kuramochi no Omi) * [[:en:Ise Province|Ise Province]] (associated with [[Kuruma Otoshigami Shrine|Kuruma Shrine]]) * [[:en:Kazusa Province|Kazusa Province]] (''[[Wamyō Ruijushō]]'' mentions Kuramochi villages in Nagara District and Habu District. Kuramochi no Kimi is linked to the descendants of Isaza no Kimi.) * [[Shimōsa Province]] (Okada District had a Kuramochi village; an inscribed earthenware from the Ikenoshita archaeological site in [[:en:Inzai|Inzai]] City reads: "Kuramochi □...second year of the □ calendar.") * [[:en:Hitachi Province|Hitachi Province]] (Makabe District contained a Kuramochi village.) * [[:en:Ōmi Province|Ōmi Province]] (The 1st-year tax ledger for Shika District mentions Kuramochi no Kimi Shimasu○; in the 2nd year, listed as Kuramochi no Kimi Shimasu○.) * [[:en:Kawachi Province|Kawachi Province]] * [[:en:Harima Province|Harima Province]] * [[Tango Province]] * [[:en:Kōzuke Province|Kōzuke Province]] (Kuruma District in Gunma Prefecture was associated.) * [[Wakasa Province]] (Kuramochi village existed in Ōi District.) * [[:en:Echizen Province|Echizen Province]] * [[:en:Etchū Province|Etchū Province]] (Kuramochi District in Niikawa existed.) * [[Tsukushi Province]]
== Notes == {{Notelist}}
