* {{ill|Settsu Province|en|Settsu Province|qid=Q864163|lt=Settsu Province|1=Settsu Province}} (''{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en|Shinsen Shōjiroku|qid=Q1045362|lt=Shinsen Shōjiroku|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}}'' records, "Kuramochi no Kimi, descendants of Toyokiiribiko no Mikoto.")
* {{ill|Iga Province|en|Iga Province|qid=Q1047128|lt=Iga Province|1=Iga Province}} (associated with Kuramochi no Omi)
* {{ill|Ise Province|en|Ise Province|qid=Q864166|lt=Ise Province|1=Ise Province}} (associated with [[Kuruma Otoshigami Shrine|Kuruma Shrine]])
* {{ill|Kazusa Province|en|Kazusa Province|qid=Q1055394|lt=Kazusa Province|1=Kazusa Province}} (''[[Wamyō Ruijushō]]'' mentions Kuramochi villages in Nagara District and Habu District. Kuramochi no Kimi is linked to the descendants of Isaza no Kimi.)
